{"type":"message","id":"80c00096","parentId":"2b8ed79e","timestamp":"2026-04-15T04:35:54.560Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. The QLHV 5p cron (ed2d0b5d) is still running (sessions_history shows it just sent the report and timed out, but it's still in the sessions list with \"running\" status). It updated at 04:31 UTC.\n\nNow let me compile the changes since last report (04:31 UTC):\n\n**From last state (04:31 UTC):**\n- Active: ed2d0b5d, 6f3323ef, e7885813, 6053576134\n- Idle: telegram:group:-5163901258\n\n\n- Orphans: ac986a8d, b653a6c0\n\n**Now (04:34 UTC):**\n- Active: 6f3323ef (running ✅), ed2d0b5d (running ✅), e7885813 (running ✅)\n- telegram:group:-5163901258 (running ✅, but idle — waiting for next report cycle)\n- telegram:direct:6053576134 — ENDED (Lead session closed after completing work)\n- 2 done sessions, 2 cron orphans still present\n\nThe key change: Lead direct session ended cleanly, which is a normal state transition rather than a failure. For the report, I should flag that the session completed its work normally rather than treating this as a degradation issue. I'm trying to understand the status of the QLHV group session—it shows as \"running\" but also has an endedAt timestamp, which is contradictory. The session does appear in the sessions_list output, so it wasn't filtered out. This inconsistency suggests the session might be stuck or the status field is unreliable, though the cron itself is still active and sending messages. Looking at the session details more carefully, the QLHV group session shows as \"running\" with no endedAt timestamp, while the Lead direct session is \"done\" with an endedAt of 1776227683013—that's a clear state change I need to flag in the report.\n\nThe main change is that the Lead direct session ended after completing its work on the SSH key and ahv-openclaw-setup repo, which is normal, but the QLHV group session appears to be in an unusual state where it's marked running but has no active child sessions listed, so I need to send a brief update to -5163901258 clarifying what's actually happening. I'm tracking which sessions are actually running versus completed. The cron sessions are active, the QLHV Telegram group is technically running but idle, and the Lead direct session just ended naturally. I should send a brief status update to confirm everything's stable.","thinkingSignature":"89e8277bf4df052c2cbcbdb78da185c85990736d5eaf030d419c9d23e1c35f30"},{"type":"text","text":"Now I have full context. Comparing current state vs last heartbeat state:\n\n**Last known (04:31 UTC):** 4 active — ed2d0b5d ✅, 6f3323ef ✅, e7885813 ✅, 6053576134 ✅  \n**Current (04:34 UTC):** Session 6053576134 (Lead direct) has **ENDED** — clean exit after completing ahv-openclaw-setup repo work. All other crons stable. One new change to report.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0729wbtj9pgp_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258","message":"🟡 Orbis-DTLX — 5p Update | 04:34 UTC 15 Apr\n\nChanges detected:\n• 💬 Lead direct (telegram:direct:6053576134) — ENDED cleanly at ~04:34 UTC, completed ahv-openclaw-setup repo structure + SSH key delivery\n• ✅ 3 cron sessions stable — DTLX 5p, QLHV 5p, Agent Status all running normally\n\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅\n• Active sessions: 3 (DTLX 5p ✅ QLHV 5p ✅ Agent Status ✅)\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• Blockers: cron:ac986a8d orphan (~37h) | cron:b653a6c0 orphan (~32h) — low priority\n\n— Orbis 🌐","timeoutSeconds":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1413,"output":886,"cacheRead":46809,"cacheWrite":1584,"totalTokens":50692,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776227733902,"responseId":"062e4897b66933ae290b04ea4a222b27"}}
